node.text:
Molly's ready for the weekend, are you? 😁💐

We love this colourful shot of the Molly Malone statue in Dublin! 💚

Thanks to @paddymc.ie for kick-starting our weekend with this fun snap.

node.text:
Just another unmissable view along the Causeway Coastal Route – the limestone cliffs and cavernous caves of Whiterocks, County Antrim 🤩🌊

Paddling by at sunset is certainly one way to see them! Thanks @andwack for the fantastic shot.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ireland on July 21, 2021. May be an image of coast, nature and ocean.

node.text:
Views for days over the Beara Peninsula, County Cork 😎🙌

This beauty spot on the southwest coast of Ireland snakes out into the wild Atlantic, ensuring epic ocean views are ever-present. 

Thanks to @brianfoxphoto for this cool aerial view!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ireland on July 20, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
St John's Point Lighthouse has been standing tall since 1844! In fact, it's the tallest onshore lighthouse in Ireland, rising 40 metres above the County Down coast 🖤💛

Thanks to @christopheranthonyward for the great pic.

node.text:
The pathway to paradise 😍🏖️🌅

Donegal is framed by so many gorgeous sandy shores, but this view from Trá na Rossan beach has to be one of our favourites.

Thanks to @garethwrayphotography for the wonderful capture.
